data.chText: 引人注目的；异乎寻常的；显著的
data.enText: interesting and unusual enough to attract attention
She bears a striking resemblance to her older sister.

data.chText: 姑娘们既聪明伶俐，又妩媚动人，跟她们的兄弟形成鲜明的对照。
data.enText: In striking contrast to their brothers, the girls were both intelligent and charming.

data.chText: 妩媚动人的；标致的；俊秀的
data.enText: very attractive, often in an unusual way

data.chText: 两次投票产生的结果截然不同。
data.enText: The two polls produced strikingly different results.

tr: the act of contacting one thing with another
example: repeated hitting raised a large bruise
after three misses she finally got a hit

tr: the physical coming together of two or more things
example: contact with the pier scraped paint from the hull

tr: having a quality that thrusts itself into attention
example: an outstanding fact of our time is that nations poisoned by anti semitism proved less fortunate in regard to their own freedom
a new theory is the most prominent feature of the book
a striking thing about Picadilly Circus is the statue of Eros in the center
a striking resemblance between parent and child

tr: sensational in appearance or thrilling in effect
example: a spectacular display of northern lights
his striking good looks always created a sensation

value.def: Something that is striking is very noticeable or unusual.

example.ex: The most striking feature of those statistics is the high proportion of suicides...
example.tran: 那些统计数据最引人注目之处是其极高的自杀率。

example.ex: He bears a striking resemblance to Lenin.

value.tran: 引人注目的;异乎寻常的;显著的

example.ex: In one respect, however, the men really were strikingly similar.
example.tran: 然而，一方面，那些男人真的非常相似。

example.ex: Most strikingly, the amount consumers spent in the shops grew much more quickly than anyone expected.
example.tran: 最惊人的是，消费者的购物支出的增长速度远远超过了任何人的预期。

value.def: Someone who is striking is very attractive, in a noticeable way.

example.ex: She was a striking woman with long blonde hair.
example.tran: 她是个留着金色长发的俏女郎。

value.tran: 妩媚动人的;标致的;俊秀的
